/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:35:The pressure P_k^{21} satisfies -Delta P_k^{21} = Sum_{i,j} partial_i partial_j [phi_k u_j(1 - v_k/|u|) u_i(1 - v_k/|u|)]. The factors u(1-v_k/|u|) are BOUNDED BY 1 (Lemma 10), so the RHS is bounded independently of U_{k-1}. By CZ/Riesz: ||P_k^{21}||_{L^q} <= C_q. No additional power of U_{k-1} can be extracted.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:46:**The pressure is not small even when the velocity is close to its level set truncation.** P_k^{21} contributes U_{k-1}^0 = 1 to the exponent, while all other terms contribute at least U_{k-1}^{1/2}.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:50:The gap is 1/6 = 3/2 - 4/3. This is NOT "small" in perturbation theory terms — it represents a qualitative failure where the current method cannot extract enough nonlinearity from the pressure's interaction with the level sets. On the pressure side, the load-bearing feature is that `||P_k^{21}||_{L^q}` stays at constant scale because its source is bounded independently of the shrinking level sets. Later work closed the chain-level slack separately by proving the Chebyshev step sharp; any remaining pressure-side loophole must therefore change the decomposition or the pairing itself, not just sharpen existing estimates.
