/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/request-equations-for-construction.md:18:**NEW (vasseur-pressure E006):** When a computational finding identifies a mechanism (e.g., DNS shows ABC flows have anomalously high beta), the follow-up literature exploration should include an explicit derivation request: "derive WHY this happens." In E006, the derivation (Lamb vector = 0 implies pressure = Bernoulli, 3 lines) provided the rigorous explanation for the DNS outlier — far more valuable than the literature survey alone. The derivation is often brief but provides the mechanism that connects the numerical observation to analytical understanding.
