/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/standard-explorer-for-literature-surveys.md:35:- **NEW (vasseur-pressure E006):** When the literature survey includes perturbation analysis or computational verification that could be done in the same exploration, consider using a math explorer instead. E006 noted: "Should have been a math explorer — the perturbation analysis and Beltrami deficit questions could have been computationally verified within this exploration." When the goal combines survey + derivation + quantitative check, a math explorer handles all three; a standard explorer handles only the first two.
