/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/adversarial-review-needs-complete-parallel-context.md:14:**vasseur-pressure S2-E007:** The adversarial reviewer flagged "non-CZ pressure handling incomplete" as a gap in the obstruction result. However, S2-E006 had already been completed in parallel and showed beta = 4/3 is tool-independent (three non-CZ routes tested, all <= 4/3). The adversarial review was launched without E006's findings because both explorations ran simultaneously.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:3:Lessons about what strategy structures work: exploration sequencing, phased approaches, when to pivot, proven patterns for specific task types, explorer-type matching, and handling negative results. **52 entries.** (NEW: **reconcile-notation-before-falsification** [far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole meta-001 — when a surviving lead is inherited across different decompositions/vocabularies, reconcile notation before falsification; prevents testing the wrong object, e.g. harmonic `P_{k1}` vs local `P_{k21}` vs Wolf-style far-field split]. Prior: tool-independence-stronger-than-single-failure [vasseur-pressure S2-E006]; quantitative-comparison-reveals-why-standard-is-standard [vasseur-pressure S2-E006]; bernstein-lp-poison-pill-3d [S2-E005]; check-bypass-not-just-improve-bottleneck [S2-E005]; distinguish-constant-from-scaling-slack [S2-E002]; model-pde-comparison-for-mechanism-identification [S2-E003]; test-improvability-before-pursuing-variations [S2-E003]; decomposition-audit-before-attacking-barrier [S2-E001]; test-generalization-before-concluding [E010]; adversarial-check-between-phases [E010/E009]; gap-finding [E005]; standard-explorer [E006]; sufficient-ic-diversity [E002].)
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:24:- **adversarial-check-between-phases.md** — Run a lightweight adversarial check after Phase 2 (before Phase 3 computation begins); early reframing is more valuable than corrections after major compute is committed. *Updated (E008): upgraded to full standard-test adversarial exploration early.* **UPDATED (vasseur-pressure E009): timing refinement — run adversarial AFTER key mechanism identified/tested but BEFORE extended tests. UPDATED (vasseur-pressure E010): adversarial -> targeted follow-up variant — adversarial identifies weakest link, then a single targeted exploration definitively tests it (E010 confirmed E009's weakest-claim assessment via perturbed-ABC sweep).**
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:31:- **include-trivial-control-checks.md** — NEW (thermal-time meta-003), UPDATED (vasseur-pressure E007): Every computation exploration should include one "should equal X by construction" check (different code path, limit case, or symmetry). The thermal-time E003 control check C_global = C_full (at machine zero for all λ) confirmed that the 82.7% discrepancy was physical, not a bug. Cost: near zero. Payoff: immediate trust or bug detection. **NEW variants (E007):** known-answer validation at exact-solution conditions (t=0 Beltrami sanity check caught sign error propagated from prior code), and verify mathematical identity before building measurements (div(u_below) != 0 invalidated prescribed Lamb decomposition).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:45:- **definition-extraction-gates-computation.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure E001), UPDATED (anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall meta-001): Before computation phases, run a definition-extraction exploration ("Phase 0") reading primary sources to verify the team's understanding of the target quantity. Prevents the most wasteful failure: computing the wrong thing due to incorrect mental model. Vasseur-pressure: team assumed beta = pressure integrability; Phase 0 revealed beta = De Giorgi recurrence exponent. **Updated variant:** if Phase 0 only needs the mechanism architecture, partial primary-source access can still be sufficient — recover operator / reduced model / theorem layers first rather than blocking on every auxiliary estimate.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:46:- **sufficient-ic-diversity-for-outliers.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure E002): For measurement campaigns, use 5+ ICs covering different structural classes (symmetric/random, 2D-like/3D, special algebraic structure, low/high intermittency). Fewer ICs risk missing qualitatively different behavior. ABC (Beltrami) was the 5th IC and produced the most important finding (beta_eff = 1.01 vs 0.35-0.73 for others). Distinct from anticipate-symmetry-degeneracies (avoiding bad ICs) and require-independent-verification-baseline (checking same answer).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:47:- **reconcile-notation-before-falsification.md** — NEW (far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole meta-001): When a surviving lead is inherited across multiple vocabularies or decompositions, reconcile notation before falsification. Prevents testing the wrong object. Example: Vasseur's harmonic `P_{k1}` vs bad local `P_{k21}` vs later Wolf-style far/near split. Distinct from decomposition-audit-before-attacking-barrier (one proof's chain) and complementary to preload-context-from-prior-work (load context + verify compatibility).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:48:- **decomposition-audit-before-attacking-barrier.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E001): Always run a line-by-line proof reading + sharpness classification before attacking a mathematical barrier. Understanding the proof structure first prevents wasting budget on provably closed directions. S2-E001: narrowed 5 open Track B directions to 1, saving 3+ explorations. Deliver: step-by-step chain, sharpness classification, sensitivity table, free parameter catalog, attack surface narrowing. Distinct from definition-extraction-gates-computation (right quantity vs. right step) and gap-finding (literature landscape vs. single proof structure).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:49:- **test-generalization-before-concluding.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure E010): When a mechanism is demonstrated for an exact special case (eigenstate, symmetry, exact solution), always test whether it extends to perturbations before treating it as a strategy conclusion. "Mechanism works for exact X" does NOT imply "mechanism works for near-X" — eigenfunction properties can be structurally fragile. E010: Beltrami B_k = O(2^{-k}) destroyed by 1% perturbation. Design a perturbation sweep (eps = 0.01 to 0.50) before concluding. Distinct from verify-identity-generalization (proof identities, not empirical mechanisms) and adversarial-check (diagnostic, not treatment).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:50:- **model-pde-comparison-for-mechanism-identification.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E003): When investigating a mathematical barrier in a specific PDE, compare the barrier across structurally related model PDEs (different dimensions, dissipation orders, nonlinearities). Reveals whether the barrier is universal (same formula across PDEs — attack the mechanism) or PDE-specific (study what the successful PDE has that the target lacks). S2-E003: comparing beta across Burgers/2DNS/SQG/MHD/fractional NS produced two major insights in one exploration — universal formula beta = 1 + s/n AND SQG exception mechanism (drift structure, not Chebyshev). Protocol: identify barrier, list 4-6 model PDEs, compute barrier for each, tabulate, identify universal formula or systematic exceptions. Distinct from comparison-exploration-pattern (two approaches to one problem, not one approach across problems) and gap-finding (within one framework, not across).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:51:- **test-improvability-before-pursuing-variations.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E003): When a decomposition audit identifies a single target step as the potential weak link, the FIRST analytical exploration should test whether that target is independently improvable (i.e., improvement is possible without solving the entire original problem). If circular with the main problem, pivot immediately. S2-E003: 6 Chebyshev improvement routes all ruled out or circular in one exploration; improving L^{10/3} to L^4 Chebyshev requires H^{5/4} regularity (the Lions threshold = the original problem). Saved 3+ explorations on Lorentz/interpolation/support tricks. Protocol: enumerate improvement routes, classify each as (a) impossible, (b) insufficient, (c) circular, or (d) open; if all (a)/(b)/(c), target is not independently improvable — pivot. Distinct from decomposition-audit (identifies target, not viability) and decisive-negative-pivot (dimensional analysis, not circularity detection).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:52:- **extract-precise-obstruction-from-failed-route.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E004): When a promising route fails, extract the PRECISE obstruction — not just "it doesn't work." The precise failure point immediately suggests the next direction. S2-E004: three independent obstructions from the commutator route (no div-curl, remainder dominance, CRW vacuous) each generated specific next leads (frequency-localized De Giorgi, div-free approximation, unbounded-but-BMO multiplier). Protocol: identify all independent obstruction layers, state precise mathematical condition that fails, state what would need to change, rank resulting leads. Distinct from decisive-negative-pivot (decision to pivot vs. information extraction) and useful-failure-extracts-secondary-results (accidental findings vs. deliberate obstruction analysis).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:53:- **numerical-spectral-dns-diagnostic.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E004): Numerical spectral analysis (frequency-resolved energy decomposition) on DNS data is a powerful diagnostic for mathematical PDE questions. Reveals whether obstructions are high-frequency or low-frequency — information invisible to analytical norms. S2-E004: commutator part had faster spectral decay but remainder dominated high frequencies by 18x at k=20, immediately identifying the analytical bottleneck. Protocol: compute decomposition on DNS, measure L^2 norms per component, compute spectral energy distribution, compare decay rates, report dominant component at high frequencies. Distinct from sufficient-ic-diversity (IC selection vs. frequency analysis) and include-trivial-control-checks (consistency vs. diagnostic).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:54:- **distinguish-constant-from-scaling-slack.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E002): When measuring "tightness" of an inequality in a De Giorgi or similar iterative proof, the key question is NOT "is there slack?" but "does the slack scale with U_{k-1}^{-delta}?" Constant multiplicative slack (ratio independent of k and U) only affects C in the recurrence, NOT beta. Only slack scaling as U_{k-1}^{-delta} can improve beta. S2-E002: De Giorgi Chebyshev tightness ratios ~3-5x and k-independent — correctly interpreted as non-transformative, but this distinction should have been in the exploration goal from the start. Protocol: measure ratio vs k, test correlation with U_{k-1}, classify as constant or scaling. Distinct from test-improvability-before-pursuing-variations (circularity of proof step, not measurement interpretation) and decomposition-audit-before-attacking-barrier (identifies target, not interprets data).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:55:- **bernstein-lp-poison-pill-3d.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E005): The Bernstein inequality exchange rate 2^{3j/5} per LP block in 3D is fixed by dimensional analysis (Sobolev embedding cost L^2_{3/10} -> L^{10/3}) and destroys any frequency-localized improvement attempt for De Giorgi iterations. General lesson for LP-based approaches to 3D PDE barriers: the conversion cost from regularity (Sobolev/Besov) to integrability (L^p) is exactly what CZ theory already accounts for. Additionally, the k-dependent character change (resonance at low k -> paraproduct at high k) means no single analytical technique handles all De Giorgi levels optimally, which may explain the 4/3 barrier's robustness. When to apply: check if Bernstein exchange rate 2^{dj(1/2-1/p)} is comparable to spectral decay; if yes, LP cannot help. Distinct from extract-precise-obstruction-from-failed-route (information extraction vs. structural recognition), numerical-spectral-dns-diagnostic (diagnostic tool vs. interpretation), and distinguish-constant-from-scaling-slack (measurement interpretation vs. tool selection).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:56:- **check-bypass-not-just-improve-bottleneck.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E005): When a bottleneck tool limits progress, always ask "can we avoid this tool entirely?" before "can we improve it?" Protocol: (1) Can we avoid using this tool at all? (2) Is there a fundamentally different tool for the same job? (3) Can we improve the tool's output? S2-E001 through S2-E005 spent 5 explorations on question 3 (improving CZ or working around it); the strategizer should have asked question 1 after S2-E001 showed all CZ-based routes are tight. Distinct from ask-what-replaces-the-bottleneck (what new bottleneck after reformulation vs. whether to use the tool at all), decomposition-audit-before-attacking-barrier (which step is tight vs. whether the framework is right), and decisive-negative-pivot (when to stop vs. what direction to go).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:57:- **tool-independence-stronger-than-single-failure.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E006): When multiple independent analytical routes to the same exponent/barrier are computed, the result upgrades from "method X doesn't work" to "the barrier is intrinsic to the problem structure." Always compute at least two alternative routes when closing a direction. S2-E006: IBP (beta=1), H^1/BMO (beta=4/3), CRW (beta<=1) — the H^1/BMO match via different mechanism establishes tool-independence of 4/3. Distinct from extract-precise-obstruction (ONE failed route), check-bypass-not-just-improve-bottleneck (whether to avoid the tool), ask-what-replaces-the-bottleneck (new bottleneck after reformulation).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/INDEX.md:58:- **quantitative-comparison-reveals-why-standard-is-standard.md** — NEW (vasseur-pressure S2-E006): When closing a direction, compute the QUANTITATIVE gap between the closed route and the standard route. The magnitude and mechanism of the gap reveal why the standard method became standard, constraining future improvement attempts. S2-E006: IBP beta=1 vs CZ beta=4/3 — gap of exactly 1/3 = CZ consolidation gain (bilinear product mapped to single L^p function enables Chebyshev extraction). Shows CZ consolidation is ESSENTIAL, not just convenient. Distinct from extract-precise-obstruction (what fails vs. why standard is better), distinguish-constant-from-scaling-slack (slack type vs. inter-route gap mechanism), tool-independence-stronger-than-single-failure (structural conclusion vs. mechanism explanation).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/require-gaussian-control-for-non-gaussian-states.md:10:When a computation involves a **non-Gaussian quantum state** and uses a **Gaussian approximation** (e.g., quadratic modular Hamiltonian from covariance matrices), always request a parallel computation with a **Gaussian control state** (coherent state excitation, squeezed vacuum, etc.) to isolate the approximation artifact from the physical effect.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/require-gaussian-control-for-non-gaussian-states.md:16:- **thermal-time strategy-002 exploration-003** — The one-particle excitation |1_m> is non-Gaussian. The Gaussian approximation produced a modular Hamiltonian that oscillates at the wrong frequencies (entanglement spectrum, not physical). The meta note identified: "The goal should have specified: 'If using Gaussian approximation, also test with a coherent state (which IS Gaussian) to isolate the approximation artifact.'" This was not done, leaving a proof gap — the structural frequency mismatch could be partially a Gaussian approximation artifact, though the magnitude makes this unlikely.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/gap-finding-in-existing-programs.md:5:source: "classicality-budget strategy-001 meta-exploration-003; stochastic-electrodynamics strategy-001 meta-exploration-003; vasseur-pressure strategy-001 meta-exploration-005"
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/gap-finding-in-existing-programs.md:22:**NEW (vasseur-pressure E005):** Include a "what has the community tried and failed at?" deliverable in literature surveys. Requesting a table of all post-X papers and their relationship to a specific problem produces decisive strategic intelligence. In E005, the table of post-2007 De Giorgi papers revealed that NO paper had attempted to improve beta beyond 4/3 — the community moved orthogonally. This confirmed the problem is hard AND that any improvement would be genuinely novel. The table format (year, authors, result, relation to target) forces completeness and makes negative results (absence of attempts) immediately visible.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/allow-analytic-extremizer-over-computation.md:4:source: "vasseur-pressure s2-meta-exploration-008"
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/definition-extraction-gates-computation.md:5:source: "vasseur-pressure strategy-001 meta-exploration-001; anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall strategy-001 meta-exploration-001"
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/definition-extraction-gates-computation.md:14:- **vasseur-pressure exploration-001** — The team assumed beta was a pressure integrability exponent. The Phase 0 exploration (reading Vasseur 2007) revealed that beta is actually a De Giorgi recurrence exponent with a completely different mathematical structure. If the team had skipped to DNS computation, they would have measured pressure integrability indices (a well-defined but irrelevant quantity) rather than the recurrence exponent that actually controls regularity. The entire computational strategy would have been wasted.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/numerical-spectral-dns-diagnostic.md:5:source: "vasseur-pressure s2-meta-004"
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/numerical-spectral-dns-diagnostic.md:14:Vasseur-pressure Strategy-002, Exploration 004: The commutator decomposition of P^{21} has two parts — the commutator terms and the divergence-error remainder. Analytically, both are O(1). But the numerical spectral decomposition revealed:
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/staged-computation-goals.md:20:1. **Independent debuggability**: If Stage 2 fails, the bug is isolated to Stage 2 code, not contaminated by Stage 3. The explorer doesn't spend time diagnosing cascading errors.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/flag-cross-framework-connections.md:5:source: "vasseur-pressure strategy-001 meta-exploration-006"
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/flag-cross-framework-connections.md:14:- **vasseur-pressure strategy-001 exploration 006** — The exploration connected geometric regularity criteria (Constantin-Fefferman 1993, Beirao da Veiga-Berselli 2002) with Vasseur's De Giorgi iteration framework. No existing paper formulates a conditional regularity result in the specific form: "If the Beltrami deficit B(u) < epsilon_0, then the De Giorgi exponent satisfies beta > 3/2." This cross-framework connection was identified as potential novel territory precisely because both frameworks are well-established but have not been combined.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/one-task-per-exploration.md:5:source: "strategy-001 meta-006, strategy-001 meta-007, strategy-001 meta-009, strategy-003 meta-s3-001, riemann-hypothesis meta-exploration-004, riemann-hypothesis s002-meta-exploration-005, riemann-hypothesis s003-meta-exploration-003, vasseur-pressure strategy-001 meta-exploration-007"
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/one-task-per-exploration.md:51:- **vasseur-pressure strategy-001 exploration-007** — Task A (Beltrami deficit vs k) and Task B (Hessian/remainder pressure decomposition) share DNS infrastructure and are conceptually linked (each informs interpretation of the other). The explorer handled both cleanly without fragmentation.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/one-task-per-exploration.md:66:When a goal contains both essential and exploratory tasks, **explicitly mark which tasks are optional and can be skipped under time pressure.** Without this, the explorer must guess priorities. With it, the explorer can correctly focus on the critical path and skip secondary tasks when time-pressured — which is usually the right call.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/one-task-per-exploration.md:72:> **Optional (skip if time-pressured):** Tasks 3, 5 (exploratory; will be dedicated explorations later)
