/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:8:- **specify-failure-paths.md** — Include "if this fails, explain why and propose alternatives" to turn negative results into positive leads; includes variants for physical implication explorations, domain constraints, per-assumption honesty, no-go framing, **formalism applicability pre-screening** (ask "can this formalism yield the modification in principle?" before committing), **explicit skip permission for ambiguous sub-tasks** (say "skip if normalization is unclear; note what you'd need" — prevents silent omission), **request structural explanation when construction may fail** (RH s002-E006 — "if the construction fails, determine if the failure is empirical or structural; if structural, provide the proof" → elicits algebraic impossibility proofs that close entire construction classes, far more valuable than numerical negatives alone), and **quantitative falsification criterion for hypothesis-testing computations** (vasseur-pressure E004 — state the falsification criterion explicitly: "if X is constant in Y, hypothesis is falsified"; seed alternative paths).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:11:- **name-specific-authors-and-papers.md** — Name target authors/papers for literature searches; combine with "and any others you find" for thoroughness. **NEW variant: "also survey related approaches by same group/school"** [vasseur-pressure E003 — most valuable finding was incidental Choi-Vasseur discovery, not the targeted Tran-Yu assessment].
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:22:- **instruct-incremental-writing.md** — Include "write section by section, not all at once" in GOAL.md to prevent multi-minute stalls. **For multi-test/staged explorations, use section-specific checkpoints: "after Test N, write Test N section before proceeding to Test N+1."** **[SECTION COMPLETE] marker variant**; **research-buffering stall is systematically unpreventable** — fix is kill + extract + manual write or split-search-from-synthesis. **Adversarial per-claim checkpoint**. NEW: **write-during-long-computation variant** [RH s003-meta-009] — for computations >15 min, submit as background job and write intermediate results first; decouples writing from computation to prevent context-pressure loss of all results. *12 confirmations across 7 missions.*
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:34:- **adversarial-synthesis-goal-structure.md** — NEW (SED s003-meta-004): 4-part output structure for finishing-strategy adversarial synthesis goals: (1) adversarial review per claim with verdict+novelty rating, (2) prior art search for the conclusion, (3) grand synthesis, (4) consolidated claims table. Pre-load all claims with evidence summaries, prior art candidates, and strongest objections directly into GOAL.md. Long goals (200-300 lines) are unavoidable and worth it. Tier 5 requires concrete falsifiable paths per claim, not just literature checks. *Updated (thermal-time s003-meta-002): prior art discovery can be the most important outcome.* **UPDATED (vasseur-pressure E009): evidence grading (A/B/C/D/F per claim) makes strength immediately visible; "weakest link" deliverable forces rank-ordering; novel claims list by adversarial reviewer (not original explorer) produces more conservative assessments; require fix specification per weakness to enable action rather than paralysis.**
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:35:- **require-gaussian-control-for-non-gaussian-states.md** — When computing with non-Gaussian states using Gaussian approximation (e.g., quadratic modular Hamiltonian from covariance matrices), always request a parallel computation with a Gaussian control state (coherent state) to isolate approximation artifacts from physical effects. **CONFIRMED (thermal-time s003-meta-001):** two-tier pattern (coherent=easy validation + squeezed=hard test) executed successfully; Gaussian caveat on excited-state modular flow finding now closed.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:38:- **verify-goal-claims-before-delegating.md** — **[NEW, YM s003-meta-005/s003-007]** Before writing GOAL.md citing a prior result (e.g., "M(Q) ≼ M(I) confirmed by E004"), verify the cited claim actually matches what the exploration found. Two-level fix: (1) strategizer re-reads REPORT.md before citing; (2) GOAL.md includes "first compute X for 3-5 random examples — if it fails, pivot." Prevented two wasted explorations in yang-mills s003. **NEW variant: "verify paper existence before citing"** [vasseur-pressure E003 — "Tran-Yu (2014, AIHP)" doesn't exist; actual program is 5 papers 2015-2021]. Distinct from preload-context (providing findings) and include-trivial-control-checks (validating code).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:41:- **distinguish-typical-vs-worst-case-bounds.md** — **[NEW, navier-stokes E006, UPDATED vasseur-pressure E002]** For bound-tightening explorations, explicitly require explorers to classify each tighter estimate as WORST-CASE BOUND (provable, usable in proofs) or TYPICAL-CASE VALUE (statistical property, not a bound). Without this, explorers present impressive typical-case improvements (C_{L,eff} ~ Re^{-3/8}) as bound tightenings when they cannot serve as proof tools. Include template: "If typical is dramatically better than worst-case, identify the structural property separating them." **NEW variant: "empirical analogue vs analytical quantity"** — when computing empirical analogues of analytical bounds, require explicit statement of what the empirical quantity IS and ISN'T (beta_eff != beta_p; the former tests smooth solutions, the latter bounds all weak solutions). Distinct from require-quantification-in-stress-tests (quantifying objections) and specify-failure-paths (handling failures).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:43:- **flag-cross-framework-connections.md** — **[NEW, vasseur-pressure E006]** When an exploration reveals a connection between two independently well-studied frameworks that have not been connected in the literature, flag this explicitly in future goals. Such connections are potential novel territory. E006: geometric regularity criteria + De Giorgi iteration = uncharted intersection. Distinct from prioritize-novelty-assessment (checking a specific result) and gap-finding (gaps within a single program).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:44:- **adversarial-review-needs-complete-parallel-context.md** — **[NEW, vasseur-pressure S2-E007]** When launching an adversarial review in parallel with constructive explorations, the reviewer may lack findings from parallel work. Either launch adversarial reviews AFTER constructive explorations complete (preferred), or include summaries of parallel work as supplementary context. S2-E007 flagged "non-CZ pressure incomplete" when S2-E006 had already resolved it. Distinct from adversarial-check-between-phases (timing), preload-context (general loading), adversarial-synthesis-goal-structure (output format).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:45:- **require-sensitivity-table-for-proof-analysis.md** — **[NEW, vasseur-pressure S2-E001]** When an exploration analyzes a proof chain, require a sensitivity table: step, mathematical tool, exponent contribution, sensitivity dβ/dδ, sharpness classification (SHARP/POTENTIALLY LOOSE/UNKNOWN), notes. Forces per-step assessment instead of global sharp/loose claims. S2-E001: table was the single most actionable output, immediately identifying Chebyshev as the only non-sharp link. Distinct from require-trend-tabulation-for-negative-results (empirical data) and use-classification-schemes (general classification). Complementary to decomposition-audit-before-attacking-barrier (when to audit vs. what format to require).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:46:- **ask-what-replaces-the-bottleneck.md** — **[NEW, vasseur-pressure E008]** When testing an alternative formulation against a known barrier, always ask "what is the NEW bottleneck?" If the same numerical barrier reappears from a different mechanism, the obstruction is structural (not formulation-specific). E008: vorticity De Giorgi eliminates pressure but 4/3 reappears from trilinear form (1/2 + 5/6). The "what replaces it?" question was the most valuable part of the goal. Distinct from specify-failure-paths (general failure handling) and comparison-exploration-pattern (comparing approaches).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:47:- **allow-analytic-extremizer-over-computation.md** — **[NEW, vasseur-pressure S2-E008]** When designing optimization-based explorations (SDP, LP, numerical optimization), allow explorers to find analytic extremizers. The computational approach should be the fallback, not the default. S2-E008: goal described ~100-line CVXPY SDP; explorer found the constant field u=(c,0,0) is a one-line extremizer that makes the SDP unnecessary. Protocol: state mathematical question clearly, specify computation as ONE possible tool, explicitly say "if you can find an analytic extremizer, do that instead." Distinct from allow-explorer-synthesis (conclusions open, not methods), check-bypass-not-just-improve-bottleneck (whether to use framework at all), specify-computation-parameters (parameters when computation IS needed).
